From: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jan 2012 10:08:16 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 188/238] MIPS: Octeon: Select USB_ARCH_HAS_OHCI and USB_ARCH_HAS_EHCI

Source: Cavium SDK 2.3-427

We have ehci/ohci, so select them here. Otherwise you cannot select
USB without PCI.

Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Integrated-by: Jiang Bin <bin.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/Kconfig |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/Kconfig b/arch/mips/Kconfig
index 9bbdd48..4acd9fd 100644
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -681,6 +681,8 @@ config CAVIUM_OCTEON_REFERENCE_BOARD
 	select ZONE_DMA32 if !WRHV
 	select HOLES_IN_ZONE
 	select ARCH_REQUIRE_GPIOLIB
+	select USB_ARCH_HAS_OHCI
+	select USB_ARCH_HAS_EHCI
 	help
 	  This option supports all of the Octeon reference boards from Cavium
 	  Networks. It builds a kernel that dynamically determines the Octeon
